    "profile": "Alpha Centauri was formed in Greeley, Colorado, USA in 1971. The three founding members included: Jess Redmon) (lead guitar / vocals ), Randy Thompson (lead vocals/keyboards), and Kurt Smith (drums/vocals ). Garth Hannum (bass guitar), originally from Wyoming, joined the band during the years 1975 through 1979.\r\n\r\nExcept for a brief period when Jess performed and recorded with Canadian musician Chad Allen (of the original Guess Who), Alpha Centauri remained together for 12 years. During this period, the band performed its characteristic “hard driving” rock at various clubs and concert halls throughout the Midwestern US. While most of these gigs were as the main act, the band did open for artists such as Styx and Uriah Heep, Chuck Berry and Jerry Lee Lewis.\r\n\r\nAfter gathering a strong following of fans in the US, the band moved to Canada and performed extensively. It was there that the band began to write more and more of its own original material. This culminated with the release in 19",
